          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1652179980444-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add the <strong>onion</strong> and <strong>tomato wedges</strong> to the dish with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> and cook for 1-2 min</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1652179983081-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1652179983081-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1652179983081-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1652179983081-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1652179983081-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>aubergine half[ves]</strong> to one side of a<strong> tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>honey </strong>and <strong>half</strong> of your <strong>harissa paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)<strong> </strong>to the middle of each aubergine half, cut side up, then spread it with the back of a spoon until coated</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 30 min or until the aubergine is soft and golden – this is your <strong>honeyed harissa aubergine</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1652179986320-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1652179986320-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1652179986320-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1652179986320-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1652179986320-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>ground turmeric</strong>, <strong>ground cumin</strong> and<strong> vegetable stock mix </strong>with the <strong>roasted garlic paste</strong> and <strong>remaining harissa paste</strong> (not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) to the dish</p><p>Add your <strong>white long grain rice </strong>and<strong> sultanas </strong>with 300ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [390ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml] </span><strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cover with a lid and put the dish in the oven for 15-20 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked – this is your<strong> tomato pilaf</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1652179988770-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1652179988770-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1652179988770-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1652179988770-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1652179988770-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, bash your <strong>pistachios</strong> in the bag with a <strong>rolling pin</strong></p><p>When the aubergine is almost done, remove the baking tray[s] from the oven and add the <strong>crushed pistachios</strong> to the other side of the tray[s]</p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for a final 2-3 min or until the pistachios are toasted and lightly golden</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1652179991436-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1652179991436-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1652179991436-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1652179991436-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1652179991436-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>To serve, top the <strong>tomato pilaf </strong>with the <strong>honeyed harissa aubergine</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>toasted pistachios</strong> and drizzle over your <strong>natural yoghurt</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
